article.headline: Tennessee Tech 85, Northwestern St. 84 OT
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Amadi McKenzie dunked with 5.9 seconds left, and Tennessee Tech downed Northwestern State 85-84 Saturday night in overtime. The Golden Eagles (17-11) kept Northwestern State (13-12) from taking a shot in the final seconds after Kennan Jones had forced overtime by scoring a layup with one second left in regulation. The game featured 17 ties. Tennessee Tech outrebounded the Demons 47-42 and could have put the game away in regulation at the free throw line. The Golden Eagles were 28-of-42 compared to 21-of-27 for Northwestern State. Belton Rivers had 35 points for Tennessee Tech. McKenzie added 17, and Daniel Northern had 11. Trey Gilder led Northwestern State with 18 points. Colby Bargeman had 14, Luke Rogers and Jones each had 10. Jones also had 10 assists.
